<subSubSection pageNumber="797" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="797">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="797">Note:</emphasis>
An illegitimate replacement name for 
<taxonomicName authority="Jacq. (1760)" authorityName="Jacq." authorityYear="1760" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Robinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sepium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="797">Robinia sepium</emphasis>
Jacq. (1760)
</taxonomicName>
, with which 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Robinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="797">R. hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is therefore homotypic. Clausen (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="797">Gentes Herb.</emphasis>
4: 287. 1940) was therefore incorrect to treat 913.2 (LINN) as the type (illustrating it as t. 185). Lavin &amp; Sousa S. (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="797">Syst. Bot. Monogr.</emphasis>
45: 93, 106. 1995) recognise both 
<taxonomicName authority="(Jacq.) Steud." authorityName="Steud." baseAuthorityName="Jacq." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Gliricidia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sepium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="797">Gliricidia sepium</emphasis>
(Jacq.) Steud.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Robinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="797">R. hispida</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
as separate species.
</paragraph>
